Subject: [PATCH] MIPS: pb44: Fix i2c-gpio GPIO descriptor table
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 4.17.4
Git-commit: 326345f995a83e326fa2e01d54bfa9a6a307bd4d

commit 326345f995a83e326fa2e01d54bfa9a6a307bd4d upstream.

I used bad names in my clumsiness when rewriting many board
files to use GPIO descriptors instead of platform data. A few
had the platform_device ID set to -1 which would indeed give
the device name "i2c-gpio".

But several had it set to >=0 which gives the names
"i2c-gpio.0", "i2c-gpio.1" ...

Fix the one affected board in the MIPS tree. Sorry.

Fixes: b2e63555592f ("i2c: gpio: Convert to use descriptors")
